Robert J. RoseProduct Design Engineer, Mechanical Engineer - @GoogleLocationSan Francisco Bay AreaIndustryConsumer ElectronicsCurrentGooglePreviousGoogle, Incase, Robert J. Rose DesignEducationThe Cooper Union for the Advancement of Science and ArtRecommendations3 people have recommended Robert J.WebsitesBlog500+ connectionsView Robert J.’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Robert J.’s Full ProfileSummaryI'm passionate about designing products. Through making physical prototypes, physics based theoretical models, 3D models in SolidWorks and ProE/Creo, and active communication with the needs of my clientele, I strive to create the best design. I'm an experienced, full cycle product development, mechanical product design engineer. I've lead the mechanical design of several projects, as well as played supporting roles.My portfolio and personal work focuses on the following:1) Sustainable Design - Saving the environment and minimizing further cost to the user down the line 2) Solutions for Urban Living - Improving and complementing the life of an individual living in a large city 3) Energy Harvest - Harnessing wasted moments and motion and converting them into usable sources of energy4) Consumer facing products which require high level aesthetic and surfacing quality.Skills:▪ Applications: SolidWorks, ProE/Creo, Windchill, Rhino3D, Matlab, Autocad,  Siemens NX, Adobe Suite, Microsoft Office, LaTeX, Catalyst, Objet Studio, Ansys Mechanical and Magnetic, Cosmos▪ Workshop: Woodwork, Metalwork, Breadboarding, 3D digitizing, Rapid Prototyping (Objet, Polyjet, Stratasys, ZCorp, FDM, SLA, SLS)▪ Special Skills: DFM, DFA, FA, DOE, Miniature Tools, Imaging Microscope, Tolerancing, GD&T, Materials Selection, FEA, Photo & Data Capture, and Sensor Setup and Analysis▪ OS: Windows, Mac, and Linux▪ Over 6000+ CAD hours loggedSpecialties: Optimization, efficiency, mechanical design, interdisciplinary engineering integration, design, presentation, invention, cross functional team leadership. A large amount of experience in SolidWorks 3d modeling & design, physical prototyping and manufacturing applications. My work has focused on consumer product design considerations with respect to human user interaction, such as ergonomics, ease of use, and product elegance. I have been told that I am a catalyst. I seek out new technologies and find the best way to integrate them.ExperienceProduct Design EngineerGoogleFebruary 2013  –  Present (4 years 6 months)Design, prototype, 3D modeling, validation testing, manufacturing of future magic. While at Google I have worked on a number of projects in the realm of consumer electronics, taking them from initial concept through to production ramp and everything in between. This includes CM, JDM/ODM, OEM manufacturing models.Product Design Engineer, Chromecast, Home, and Living Room ProductsGoogleMay 2014  –  Present (3 years 3 months)Worked on Mechanical system design for Chromecast hardware products. This includes magnetic system, thermal system, RF shielding system, cosmetic plastics, PCB MCO, general architecture, power adapters. Involved from pre-concept through to MP and beyond. Detailed design, analysis, validation and manufacturing.Worked on Mechanical system design for Google Home. Includes, UI System design, button design, fabric grille design and sourcing, cosmetic plastics and coatings, PCB MCO, general architecture. Involved in leading concept definition and trade-off discussions. Detailed analysis, validation, manufacturing and full documentation.Product Design Engineer, Android @Home, Android NexusGoogleFebruary 2013  –  May 2014 (1 year 4 months)Mechanical EngineerIncaseSeptember 2010  –  February 2013 (2 years 6 months)San Francisco Bay AreaFreelance Product Design, Engineering & DevelopmentRobert J. Rose DesignFebruary 2008  –  February 2013 (5 years 1 month)Greater New York City AreaContract Mechanical EngineerION DesignJuly